@c ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@cindex overview
@cindex polyglot binary

@command{oci2bin} converts any Docker or OCI image into a single,
self-contained ELF64 executable.  The output requires only @command{tar}
on the target machine—no Docker daemon, no container runtime, no
installation.

The output file is also a valid POSIX tar archive accepted by
@command{docker load}, making it a polyglot binary (@pxref{How It
Works}).

@example
oci2bin alpine:latest      # produces ./alpine_latest
./alpine_latest            # runs the container
docker load < alpine_latest
@end example

Containers run rootlessly using Linux user namespaces.  The process
appears as UID@tie{}0 inside the container; on the host it runs as the
invoking user with no elevated privileges.

