@node Cross-Architecture Builds
@section Cross-Architecture Builds

@cindex aarch64
@cindex cross compilation
@opindex --arch

Build for a foreign architecture with @option{--arch}:

@example
# Install cross-compiler (Fedora)
sudo dnf install gcc-aarch64-linux-gnu sysroot-aarch64-fc43-glibc

oci2bin --arch aarch64 alpine:latest
@end example

The sysroot defaults to @file{/usr/aarch64-redhat-linux/sys-root/fc43}.
Override with the @env{AARCH64_SYSROOT} environment variable.

Supported values for @option{--arch}: @code{x86_64}, @code{aarch64}.

@node Injecting Files at Build Time
@section Injecting Files at Build Time

@opindex --add-file
@opindex --add-dir

Use @option{--add-file HOST:CONTAINER} and @option{--add-dir
HOST:CONTAINER} to embed files or directories into the image at build
time, without needing a volume mount at runtime:

@example
oci2bin --add-file ./myapp.conf:/etc/myapp/myapp.conf myapp:latest
oci2bin --add-file /etc/ssl/certs/ca-bundle.crt:/etc/ssl/certs/ca-bundle.crt base:latest
oci2bin --add-dir ./config:/etc/myapp myapp:latest
@end example

Files are added as a new layer on top of the existing image layers.
Both flags may be repeated.

@node Merging Image Layers
@section Merging Image Layers

@opindex --layer

Use @option{--layer IMAGE} to overlay additional images on top of the
base:

@example
oci2bin --layer debugtools:latest myapp:latest myapp-debug
@end example

Layers are applied in order.  The image config (@code{Cmd},
@code{Entrypoint}, @code{Env}) from the last @option{--layer} argument
overrides the base if non-null.  May be repeated.

@node Stripping Images
@section Stripping Images

@opindex --strip

@option{--strip} removes documentation, man pages, locale data, and
package caches before packaging:

@example
oci2bin --strip ubuntu:22.04 my-ubuntu
@end example

Removed path prefixes: @file{usr/share/doc/}, @file{usr/share/man/},
@file{usr/share/info/}, @file{usr/share/locale/},
@file{usr/share/i18n/}, @file{var/cache/apt/},
@file{var/lib/apt/lists/}, @file{tmp/}.

@node OCI Image Layout
@section Using OCI Image Layout

@opindex --oci-dir
@cindex skopeo
@cindex crane

Use @option{--oci-dir DIR} to build from an OCI image layout directory
instead of pulling via Docker.  Compatible with @command{skopeo},
@command{crane}, @command{buildah}, and other OCI-compliant tools:

@example
skopeo copy docker://redis:7-alpine oci:./redis-oci:latest
oci2bin --oci-dir ./redis-oci redis:7-alpine redis_7-alpine
@end example

The @var{IMAGE} argument is optional when @option{--oci-dir} is given
and is used only for the output filename default and embedded metadata.

@node Caching
@section Caching

@opindex --cache
@cindex cache

@option{--cache} stores the output binary in
@file{~/.cache/oci2bin/@var{image}_@var{digest}/output} so that
repeated builds of the same image are instant:

@example
oci2bin --cache alpine:latest   # builds and caches
oci2bin --cache alpine:latest   # returns cached binary immediately
@end example

The cache key includes the first 12 hex characters of the image's
sha256 digest, so tag updates produce a fresh cache entry.

Use the @code{list} and @code{prune} subcommands to manage the cache
(@pxref{Subcommands}).

@node Digest Pinning
@section Reproducible Builds and Digest Pinning

After pulling, oci2bin prints the content-addressed digest to stderr:

@example
oci2bin: image digest: redis@@sha256:abc123...
@end example

When @option{--cache} is active, the cache key includes the digest so
that @code{redis:latest} updates produce a fresh cache entry rather than
reusing a stale binary.

