@node Process Management
@chapter Process Management

@menu
* Init Process::
* Background Detach::
@end menu

@node Init Process
@section Init Process and Zombie Reaping

@opindex --init
@cindex zombie reaping
@cindex PID 1

@option{--init} runs a tiny zombie-reaping init as PID@tie{}1.  The
entrypoint is forked as a child; the parent loops reaping zombies.
@code{SIGTERM}, @code{SIGINT}, @code{SIGHUP}, @code{SIGUSR1}, and
@code{SIGUSR2} are forwarded to the child.  When the main child exits,
remaining zombies are drained and the exit status is returned.

@example
./my-app --init
./my-app --init --detach   # fully-managed background service
@end example

@node Background Detach
@section Running in Background

@opindex --detach

@option{--detach} (or @option{-d}) forks the container to the
background, prints the child PID to stdout, and exits.  The child calls
@code{setsid(2)} to detach from the terminal and redirects stdin from
@file{/dev/null}.

@example
PID=$(./redis --detach)
echo "Redis running as PID $PID"
sleep 1
kill "$PID"
@end example

